- Rianne and Lorna are here.
- I'll put it on your account, Captain.

1020
01:01:17,893 --> 01:01:18,882
Hey, honey.

1021
01:01:19,453 --> 01:01:21,842
What's going on?
I came home to change my shirt...

1022
01:01:27,333 --> 01:01:28,243
Why are you here?

1023
01:01:28,693 --> 01:01:29,921
They took the Hongs.

1024
01:01:37,733 --> 01:01:38,722
Shit!

1025
01:01:40,053 --> 01:01:41,247
Drop it.

1026
01:01:54,933 --> 01:01:56,651
Girls, get out!

1027
01:02:01,173 --> 01:02:02,652
Look who we got here.

1028
01:02:02,973 --> 01:02:04,770
- Uncle Benny's friend.
- Hey, Bruce.

1029
01:02:05,773 --> 01:02:07,126
Nice pajamas.

1030
01:02:08,933 --> 01:02:10,651
Where are the Hongs?

1031
01:02:18,533 --> 01:02:19,886
Drop your guns.

1032
01:02:20,373 --> 01:02:22,568
- Drop them!
- Okay, take it easy.

1033
01:02:22,973 --> 01:02:25,248
Don't stand for that, honey.

1034
01:02:32,413 --> 01:02:33,289
Son of a bitch!

1035
01:04:02,613 --> 01:04:04,171
Let the women go.

1036
01:04:23,413 --> 01:04:25,005
I can't breathe!

1037
01:04:54,773 --> 01:04:55,842
Son of a bitch!

1038
01:05:17,733 --> 01:05:19,371
I'll be damned!
Thanks, kid!

1039
01:05:24,773 --> 01:05:26,172
Ping, cut us loose!

1040
01:05:32,613 --> 01:05:33,602
Cut me loose!

1041
01:05:35,893 --> 01:05:37,246
Go ahead, cut me.

1042
01:06:17,893 --> 01:06:19,326
It's all right.

1043
01:06:20,333 --> 01:06:21,527
You okay, honey?

1044
01:06:21,973 --> 01:06:23,691
I owe you one, kid.

1045
01:06:24,213 --> 01:06:27,489
- The keys to your car?
- They're in the car.

1046
01:06:28,493 --> 01:06:29,562
We need a radio.

1047
01:06:34,173 --> 01:06:35,401
We have to go.

1048
01:06:37,053 --> 01:06:40,363
How will we find them?
We got to catch them assholes!

1049
01:06:46,653 --> 01:06:50,362
<i>- 3-William-56, this is Air 12.</i>
- We need your eyes, guys.

1050
01:06:50,733 --> 01:06:53,805
Looking for a black Mercedes
and a black Continental.

1051
01:06:54,133 --> 01:06:56,647
<i>Vicinity of Ladera at the 210 freeway.</i>

1052
01:06:56,933 --> 01:06:59,049
Black Mercedes and black Continental?

1053
01:06:59,333 --> 01:07:02,086
<i>Shouldn 't be hard</i>
<i>to find in this town.</i>

1054
01:07:02,333 --> 01:07:04,483
Just give it a shot, will you?

1055
01:07:04,733 --> 01:07:06,724
<i>- Be cooperative.</i>
- That's a roger.

1056
01:07:16,853 --> 01:07:18,332
Will wonders never cease?

1057
01:07:18,653 --> 01:07:22,362
<i>We've got 2 black Mercedes,</i>
<i>one heading east, one west.</i>

1058
01:07:23,053 --> 01:07:25,248
<i>Eastbound's on the Valley View ramp.</i>

1059
01:07:26,733 --> 01:07:28,769
We'll take it.
Locate the Continental.

1060
01:07:30,093 --> 01:07:32,084
- Is it the right one?
- I don't know.

1061
01:07:32,333 --> 01:07:34,210
We're going east and China's east.

1062
01:07:34,533 --> 01:07:36,364
- China's west too.
- We can't divide.

1063
01:07:36,613 --> 01:07:37,523
Think positive!

1064
01:07:42,213 --> 01:07:43,248
You crossed two lanes!

1065
01:07:43,653 --> 01:07:44,608
You see him?

1066
01:07:51,773 --> 01:07:53,411
Watch the road!

1067
01:07:53,853 --> 01:07:55,764
I'd give my right arm for a siren!

1068
01:07:59,893 --> 01:08:01,690
Why'd they take the Hongs?

1069
01:08:02,013 --> 01:08:04,573
Maybe they're shaking them down
for more money.

1070
01:08:07,733 --> 01:08:11,089
Hong's uncle paid already.
He got in touch with his uncle.

1071
01:08:11,453 --> 01:08:14,570
He left him a message.
It's how they know where I live.

1072
01:08:23,933 --> 01:08:26,652
There's the son of a bitch right there!

1073
01:08:26,973 --> 01:08:29,851
Bastards left us to burn!
I want to talk with them.

1074
01:08:30,173 --> 01:08:32,004
You don't have any guns!

1075
01:08:32,253 --> 01:08:33,572
Get me near this trailer.

1076
01:08:33,853 --> 01:08:34,683
But you're driving!

1077
01:08:34,893 --> 01:08:35,882
No, you're driving!

1078
01:08:36,093 --> 01:08:38,288
There's cruise control.
Just steer!

1079
01:08:38,693 --> 01:08:40,604
Why make shit complicated?

1080
01:08:48,453 --> 01:08:50,921
Closer. Don't be shy.
Get up there!

1081
01:08:52,773 --> 01:08:54,445
Closer! Closer!

1082
01:08:54,693 --> 01:08:55,762
That's it!

1083
01:09:28,253 --> 01:09:29,572
Here, asshole!
Come in!

1084
01:09:32,893 --> 01:09:35,726
I need to ask you something.
Where's the Hongs?

1085
01:10:08,573 --> 01:10:10,643
Where's the Hongs?
Where are they?

1086
01:10:17,573 --> 01:10:18,483
Get him!

1087
01:10:47,013 --> 01:10:50,562
<i>Highway Patrol, this is William-356,</i>
<i>southbound on highway!</i>

1088
01:10:51,173 --> 01:10:53,050
<i>Officer in trouble!</i>
<i>Oversized trailer.</i>

1089
01:10:55,013 --> 01:10:56,890
LAPD! Pull over! LAPD!

1090
01:10:57,813 --> 01:10:59,292
LAPD! Pull over!

1091
01:11:03,053 --> 01:11:04,532
Pull over! See that?!

1092
01:11:04,933 --> 01:11:06,366
Right! Fuck you!

1093
01:11:07,893 --> 01:11:11,363
I got an ass with a phony badge
trying to pull me over!

1094
01:11:34,573 --> 01:11:36,006
Get away from my boy!

1095
01:11:52,573 --> 01:11:53,562
Son of a bitch!

1096
01:11:56,693 --> 01:11:57,728
I got you!

1097
01:12:06,813 --> 01:12:08,212
Get in here!

1098
01:12:16,693 --> 01:12:18,570
Get the fuck in here!

1099
01:12:18,893 --> 01:12:19,882
Ready?

1100
01:12:25,133 --> 01:12:27,249
- Welcome back.
- What a drag!

1101
01:12:27,453 --> 01:12:29,728
- Thanks, Rog.
- And the Hongs?

1102
01:12:29,933 --> 01:12:31,571
We'll ask the other guy. Go!

1103
01:12:41,013 --> 01:12:42,810
Pull over! Son of a bitch!

1104
01:12:48,293 --> 01:12:50,170
Keep your hands inside, then!

1105
01:13:14,253 --> 01:13:15,288
Out of the way!

1106
01:13:16,973 --> 01:13:18,486
Wait! There he is!

1107
01:13:18,733 --> 01:13:19,882
Keep going!

1108
01:13:38,893 --> 01:13:39,928
We're gaining!

1109
01:13:40,333 --> 01:13:41,448
I got him!

1110
01:14:05,413 --> 01:14:06,402
You okay?

1111
01:14:06,653 --> 01:14:09,042
Yeah, I think
my heart's still beating.

1112
01:14:15,733 --> 01:14:17,530
Maybe a little too close.

1113
01:14:21,853 --> 01:14:24,367
<i>You are now entering an</i>
<i>international holding area.</i>

1114
01:14:24,733 --> 01:14:27,247
<i>Please have proper documentation ready.</i>

1115
01:14:59,053 --> 01:15:00,042
General.

1116
01:15:00,533 --> 01:15:01,886
Are you armed?

1117
01:15:17,613 --> 01:15:19,683
When will you have
the money for their release?

1118
01:15:20,293 --> 01:15:21,328
Very soon.

1119
01:16:12,973 --> 01:16:15,362
Brother... it's been a long time.

1120
01:16:15,813 --> 01:16:17,804
It'll be our time again soon.

1121
01:16:19,413 --> 01:16:21,688
America has many laws.

1122
01:16:21,933 --> 01:16:26,211
But written by men.

1123
01:16:26,893 --> 01:16:30,010
Money can change everything.

1124
01:17:04,933 --> 01:17:07,493
- Sorry about your loss.
- Thank you.

1125
01:17:09,093 --> 01:17:10,321
How's my hero?

1126
01:17:10,653 --> 01:17:13,929
He's a little sad,
talking about his mom and dad.

1127
01:17:18,053 --> 01:17:19,247
Here's Butters.

1128
01:17:23,693 --> 01:17:24,967
How's it going?

1129
01:17:25,213 --> 01:17:26,123
Why are you here?

1130
01:17:26,413 --> 01:17:30,042
I heard it on the radio.
I'm sorry about your house.

1131
01:17:32,173 --> 01:17:33,811
This is Detective...

1132
01:17:34,093 --> 01:17:35,651
Butters.

1133
01:17:35,893 --> 01:17:37,372
Trish, my wife.

1134
01:17:37,653 --> 01:17:39,723
Nick, Carrie...

1135
01:17:39,973 --> 01:17:40,962
...Rianne.

1136
01:17:41,253 --> 01:17:42,242
Everybody okay?

1137
01:17:44,293 --> 01:17:45,931
You know who did this?

1138
01:17:46,173 --> 01:17:47,401
It was Benny.

1139
01:17:48,733 --> 01:17:50,166
Leo!

1140
01:17:50,613 --> 01:17:53,366
- You got a phone?
- The little Fonzie guy?

1141
01:17:53,733 --> 01:17:54,882
That's him.

1142
01:17:55,493 --> 01:17:58,132
- You be okay?
- We'll be all right.

1143
01:17:58,693 --> 01:17:59,728
Call me.

1144
01:18:02,533 --> 01:18:05,331
He's there?
We'll be right there.

1145
01:18:05,573 --> 01:18:09,248
- Butters, can you drive us?
- Yeah, let's do it.

1146
01:18:09,653 --> 01:18:12,042
Leo's got him at the dentist.
Let's go!

1147
01:18:16,013 --> 01:18:17,128
Sit down.

1148
01:18:23,413 --> 01:18:24,448
<i>Captain Murtaugh...</i>

1149
01:18:25,053 --> 01:18:28,011
...I know this is a bad time...

1150
01:18:28,453 --> 01:18:31,126
...but there's something
you need to know about me.

1151
01:18:31,893 --> 01:18:34,361
I think I know what it is.

1152
01:18:34,613 --> 01:18:35,807
You do?

1153
01:18:37,053 --> 01:18:38,532
It's okay.

1154
01:18:39,333 --> 01:18:40,607
It is?

1155
01:18:40,853 --> 01:18:43,048
People have the right to do
what makes them happy.

1156
01:18:43,333 --> 01:18:45,449
Just don't expect me to like it.

1157
01:18:46,173 --> 01:18:47,970
I know this must be hard for you.

1158
01:18:48,293 --> 01:18:49,408
It's impossible for me!

1159
01:18:50,813 --> 01:18:54,283
I hoped we'd get together
for the holidays, say Christmas.

1160
01:18:54,653 --> 01:18:58,646
Why should we get together
and see each other on Christmas?

1161
01:18:59,253 --> 01:19:01,403
- I'm trying to reach out.
- Reach somewhere else!

1162
01:19:01,813 --> 01:19:04,088
Do what you want,
but leave me out of it.

1163
01:19:04,413 --> 01:19:06,973
- I got it.
- I don't want to hear about it.

1164
01:19:07,333 --> 01:19:08,482
Not a word.

1165
01:19:08,733 --> 01:19:12,772
Why you grinning?
Think about how we can talk to Benny.

1166
01:19:13,213 --> 01:19:14,851
I got it all worked out.

1167
01:19:15,613 --> 01:19:17,046
What's the matter?

1168
01:19:17,493 --> 01:19:18,482
My ass hurts.

1169
01:19:18,733 --> 01:19:20,769
My tooth!
Is this a dentist or proctologist?

1170
01:19:21,293 --> 01:19:23,853
- Please be quiet.
- I'm trying! I'm in pain!

1171
01:19:24,133 --> 01:19:26,772
Why don't you go see
your own dentist?

1172
01:19:27,133 --> 01:19:29,408
My dentist's in Detroit or I'd go!

1173
01:19:29,693 --> 01:19:32,161
- Oh, brother!
- Oh, brother?! Get the dentist!

1174
01:19:33,213 --> 01:19:35,773
I'm sorry to bother you.
It's an emergency.

1175
01:19:36,093 --> 01:19:38,129
A man walked in off the street.

1176
01:19:38,373 --> 01:19:40,841
He's in a lot of pain.
You better come.

1177
01:19:45,013 --> 01:19:47,322
Okay, you can come in now!

1178
01:19:55,173 --> 01:19:58,848
- Leo can pull this off?
- Leo's got a B.S. In B.S.

1179
01:20:00,813 --> 01:20:02,246
Coast is clear.

1180
01:20:03,973 --> 01:20:05,884
Talk to the hand!
One second.

1181
01:20:06,573 --> 01:20:09,645
- Wait a minute.
- Let me do my job!

1182
01:20:10,053 --> 01:20:12,772
You hurt me, I'll stick
an egg roll up your ass.

1183
01:20:20,013 --> 01:20:22,322
Don't be alarmed.
It's only a drill.

1184
01:20:22,653 --> 01:20:23,642
Don't say a word.

1185
01:20:24,053 --> 01:20:25,042
Shut up.

1186
01:20:26,333 --> 01:20:29,609
Where are the Hongs?
Open wide and tell me.

1187
01:20:29,853 --> 01:20:31,081
I don't know any Hongs.

1188
01:20:31,373 --> 01:20:33,967
Their uncle paid you
to get them out of China.

1189
01:20:34,253 --> 01:20:36,244
More smuggling?
We went through that.

1190
01:20:36,493 --> 01:20:37,767
We're going through it again.

1191
01:20:38,133 --> 01:20:39,566
I have nothing to say.

1192
01:20:39,973 --> 01:20:41,964
These look very interesting.

1193
01:20:42,213 --> 01:20:43,566
You're not going to use it.

1194
01:20:43,973 --> 01:20:45,201
You won't shoot me.

1195
01:20:45,453 --> 01:20:47,489
- You're lousy cops.
- We're good cops.

1196
01:20:50,053 --> 01:20:51,247
This will settle him down.

1197
01:20:51,653 --> 01:20:53,769
Breathe, Uncle Benny.
Breathe!

1198
01:20:54,733 --> 01:20:55,848
Crank up the nitrous.

1199
01:20:56,533 --> 01:20:57,727
Crank that baby up.

1200
01:20:58,013 --> 01:20:59,685
You said it wouldn't hurt!

1201
01:21:00,013 --> 01:21:01,332
I'm holding this. Go ahead.

1202
01:21:01,973 --> 01:21:04,043
Deep! Right down to your toes.

1203
01:21:11,053 --> 01:21:13,169
- He's wasted!
- Have some more.

1204
01:21:13,533 --> 01:21:15,205
He'll talk.

1205
01:21:16,093 --> 01:21:17,572
Good, breathe.

1206
01:21:21,173 --> 01:21:22,845
- That's me.
- That's you.

1207
01:21:25,133 --> 01:21:27,363
Now, where are the Hongs?

1208
01:21:30,573 --> 01:21:32,882
- What's <i>renminbi</i> mean?
<i>- Renminbi</i> means...

1209
01:21:33,133 --> 01:21:34,088
<i>... renminbi.</i>

1210
01:21:34,453 --> 01:21:37,206
- You're a funny guy.
- This guy's wasting our time.

1211
01:21:37,533 --> 01:21:38,522
Time!

1212
01:21:39,093 --> 01:21:41,049
Time for Four Fathers!

1213
01:21:41,333 --> 01:21:42,925
Washington, Jefferson?
Those guys?

1214
01:21:43,253 --> 01:21:44,242
Roosevelt?

1215
01:21:45,173 --> 01:21:47,323
I'm sleeping with my wife's 2 sisters.

1216
01:21:47,733 --> 01:21:48,927
You lucky son of a bitch!

1217
01:21:49,253 --> 01:21:50,447
That's a good one.

1218
01:21:51,253 --> 01:21:52,402
Not so good...

1219
01:21:52,813 --> 01:21:54,531
...when my wife finds out.

1220
01:21:56,693 --> 01:21:59,161
I don't need needles!

1221
01:22:01,493 --> 01:22:03,563
Let's shoot his legs with Novocain...

1222
01:22:03,813 --> 01:22:06,247
...and watch him
try to get out of here.

1223
01:22:08,773 --> 01:22:10,968
What you got in your hands there?

1224
01:22:11,253 --> 01:22:12,447
A nut cup.

1225
01:22:13,693 --> 01:22:15,331
I got some big nuts!

1226
01:22:18,213 --> 01:22:19,487
That's nitrous...

1227
01:22:20,213 --> 01:22:21,487
...oxide!

1228
01:22:22,453 --> 01:22:23,772
Laughing gas!

1229
01:22:24,133 --> 01:22:25,851
We're stoned!

1230
01:22:29,973 --> 01:22:31,531
Murtaugh! Hurry up!

1231
01:22:31,933 --> 01:22:34,925
That's one funny son-in-law
you got there, Rog.

1232
01:22:35,573 --> 01:22:37,006
After tonight it be too late.

1233
01:22:37,333 --> 01:22:38,971
Too late for what?

1234
01:22:41,253 --> 01:22:42,925
Why'd you call him my son-in-law?

1235
01:22:43,293 --> 01:22:44,965
Uncle Benny? He's too old.

1236
01:22:47,173 --> 01:22:50,006
Buy Four Fathers back
at Four Fathers' store.

1237
01:22:50,893 --> 01:22:52,929
Why's he talking about his ancestors?

1238
01:22:53,173 --> 01:22:54,492
I don't know.

1239
01:22:55,173 --> 01:22:57,243
Why you call him my son-in-law?

1240
01:22:57,733 --> 01:22:58,927
Because I am!

1241
01:23:04,293 --> 01:23:05,521
I thought he was...

1242
01:23:08,453 --> 01:23:09,727
No, I'm...

1243
01:23:12,173 --> 01:23:13,162
Bloody marvelous!

1244
01:23:13,853 --> 01:23:15,969
Your baby is having my baby.

1245
01:23:17,573 --> 01:23:20,292
My baby is having his baby.

1246
01:23:20,693 --> 01:23:23,002
And your baby? Whoa, baby!

1247
01:23:23,333 --> 01:23:24,766
Whoa, baby! My baby!

1248
01:23:25,813 --> 01:23:27,610
What are you doing?

1249
01:23:27,813 --> 01:23:29,963
I couldn't stall anymore.

1250
01:23:30,893 --> 01:23:32,451
What happened?

1251
01:23:33,613 --> 01:23:35,683
Rog, look at this.
Does that hurt?

1252
01:23:43,413 --> 01:23:46,769
Uncle Benny,
anything happens to the Hongs...

1253
01:23:46,973 --> 01:23:48,929
...we'll come back
and rip you a new one.

1254
01:23:49,133 --> 01:23:50,691
That's two for Benny.

1255
01:23:51,053 --> 01:23:52,725
Bloody marvelous!

1256
01:23:56,213 --> 01:23:58,602
- Are you crazy?
- Why did you do that?

1257
01:23:58,853 --> 01:24:00,809
For keeping it from me
and letting me think...

1258
01:24:01,173 --> 01:24:02,845
Hit him, not me.

1259
01:24:03,093 --> 01:24:06,369
As soon as we find the Hongs,
we're getting into this.

1260
01:24:52,053 --> 01:24:52,883
Uncle.

1261
01:24:53,413 --> 01:24:54,562
You're all here?

1262
01:24:54,853 --> 01:24:56,127
All here.

1263
01:24:57,813 --> 01:24:59,212
What's going on?

1264
01:24:59,533 --> 01:25:01,922
As payment for bringing you
to America...

1265
01:25:02,133 --> 01:25:04,124
...your uncle's working for us.

1266
01:25:05,013 --> 01:25:06,207
Now finish the job.

1267
01:25:06,453 --> 01:25:08,250
What job?

1268
01:25:08,893 --> 01:25:10,531
No time to talk now.

1269
01:25:10,773 --> 01:25:12,843
Take them to their new homes...

1270
01:25:13,093 --> 01:25:15,653
...and guarantee their safety.
Then I'll finish.

1271
01:25:29,293 --> 01:25:33,366
Finish now or watch the others die.

1272
01:25:49,973 --> 01:25:51,406
<i>Rimminy</i>?

1273
