- I'll be behind you.

1521
01:48:47,653 --> 01:48:49,928
You picked a strange angel, honey.

1522
01:48:52,013 --> 01:48:53,651
But I got the message.

1523
01:48:54,893 --> 01:48:56,406
I got the message.

1524
01:49:02,413 --> 01:49:04,244
I'll always have this.

1525
01:49:04,813 --> 01:49:06,166
Always have you.

1526
01:49:06,813 --> 01:49:08,405
In here and here.

1527
01:49:09,933 --> 01:49:10,763
Thanks, honey.

1528
01:49:11,133 --> 01:49:13,010
I got to go. Bye.

1529
01:49:13,653 --> 01:49:15,291
I am not ready to have this baby!

1530
01:49:15,653 --> 01:49:17,928
You're as ready as you're going to be.

1531
01:49:18,293 --> 01:49:19,726
Fine! Just wheel me in.

1532
01:49:20,173 --> 01:49:22,209
My legs are staying closed!

1533
01:49:23,133 --> 01:49:24,043
Give me this!

1534
01:49:24,413 --> 01:49:25,766
Ma'am, let go!

1535
01:49:26,173 --> 01:49:29,006
I am a police officer!
And I am not ready!

1536
01:49:35,373 --> 01:49:36,567
Are you all right?

1537
01:49:36,933 --> 01:49:38,286
- Are you the husband?
- Yes.

1538
01:49:38,573 --> 01:49:39,688
Honey, are you all right?

1539
01:49:39,893 --> 01:49:40,803
No, I'm not.

1540
01:49:41,133 --> 01:49:42,885
I said I didn't want
to get married, but I do.

1541
01:49:43,213 --> 01:49:45,807
I want to be a wife
before I'm a mother.

1542
01:49:46,133 --> 01:49:47,282
I know you don't want to.

1543
01:49:49,293 --> 01:49:50,851
- You said "okay"?
- Yes, I did. Okay.

1544
01:49:51,253 --> 01:49:52,652
Let's do it.

1545
01:49:53,733 --> 01:49:55,007
He said okay.

1546
01:49:55,533 --> 01:49:57,683
- Congratulations.
- He said okay, Leo.

1547
01:49:58,133 --> 01:49:59,486
Oh, my God!

1548
01:49:59,853 --> 01:50:01,366
What's that smell?

1549
01:50:01,733 --> 01:50:04,645
I was on my way to the toilet
and she grabbed me.

1550
01:50:04,853 --> 01:50:07,526
- I'm so sorry.
- Have a nice baby!

1551
01:50:09,293 --> 01:50:10,612
I'm so sorry.

1552
01:50:13,453 --> 01:50:15,205
Will you marry me?

1553
01:50:18,533 --> 01:50:19,522
You bet I will.

1554
01:50:22,693 --> 01:50:23,569
Let's go.

1555
01:50:23,933 --> 01:50:26,242
I'm not going! Wait!

1556
01:50:27,853 --> 01:50:29,002
- Get a minister.
- Now?

1557
01:50:29,213 --> 01:50:32,046
Now. We're getting married.
Here comes another one.

1558
01:50:32,293 --> 01:50:33,282
We need a license...

1559
01:50:33,533 --> 01:50:35,524
I want to hear it
before the baby comes!

1560
01:50:35,733 --> 01:50:36,643
It's coming now.

1561
01:50:37,013 --> 01:50:39,527
Listen, I am getting married
or there is no baby.

1562
01:50:39,813 --> 01:50:42,202
This could be an aspect
of a transition phase.

1563
01:50:42,453 --> 01:50:45,251
This is no goddamn aspect
of a transition phase!

1564
01:50:45,613 --> 01:50:47,251
Honey, everybody, calm down.

1565
01:50:47,613 --> 01:50:49,092
Calm down. Okay?

1566
01:50:49,453 --> 01:50:51,728
Get a priest, minister, anything.

1567
01:50:52,053 --> 01:50:54,362
Go get a priest!
Goddamn it, Leo!

1568
01:50:54,733 --> 01:50:56,325
I got it. Okay.

1569
01:50:56,653 --> 01:50:58,530
Pant, pant, blow.
Remember Lamaze class?

1570
01:50:58,813 --> 01:51:00,451
Pant, blow. Come on!

1571
01:51:02,533 --> 01:51:04,012
But I want to say "I do."

1572
01:51:04,333 --> 01:51:06,005
Here he is!

1573
01:51:06,333 --> 01:51:07,561
This is Rabbi Gelb.

1574
01:51:07,853 --> 01:51:08,763
A rabbi?

1575
01:51:09,013 --> 01:51:10,366
You said anything.

1576
01:51:10,733 --> 01:51:11,882
He'll do.

1577
01:51:12,133 --> 01:51:13,612
For what I'll do?

1578
01:51:13,853 --> 01:51:16,083
We'd like you to marry us.
Please.

1579
01:51:16,373 --> 01:51:17,806
- You're Jewish?
- Not necessarily.

1580
01:51:18,133 --> 01:51:19,327
- You got a license?
- No.

1581
01:51:19,613 --> 01:51:21,285
Please don't go!

1582
01:51:21,933 --> 01:51:24,493
She needs to hear the words
before the baby comes.

1583
01:51:24,773 --> 01:51:28,209
Are you both serious?
I don't have time for hijinks.

1584
01:51:28,493 --> 01:51:29,721
We're very serious.

1585
01:51:30,053 --> 01:51:31,884
I could do it.
It wouldn't be official.

1586
01:51:32,173 --> 01:51:33,652
I just want to hear the words.

1587
01:51:34,053 --> 01:51:35,930
What the hell! Your names?

1588
01:51:36,293 --> 01:51:37,646
I'm Martin and this is Lorna.

1589
01:51:38,093 --> 01:51:39,492
Martin and Lorna.

1590
01:51:40,293 --> 01:51:42,966
What am I doing?
How do the <i>goyim</i> do this?

1591
01:51:44,293 --> 01:51:46,090
Dearly beloved!

1592
01:51:46,373 --> 01:51:50,844
Dearly beloved,
marriage is a spiritual union...

1593
01:51:52,013 --> 01:51:54,846
Faster!
She's heading for the home stretch.

1594
01:51:55,213 --> 01:51:57,329
Martin, will you take
Lorna to be your wife?

1595
01:51:57,613 --> 01:52:00,889
Will you honor, love, etc...

1596
01:52:01,133 --> 01:52:03,089
...till death do you part?
- I will.

1597
01:52:03,293 --> 01:52:05,887
Lorna, will you take Martin
to be your husband?

1598
01:52:06,253 --> 01:52:08,721
- I do.
- The same thing.

1599
01:52:08,933 --> 01:52:10,082
I pronounce you man and wife.

1600
01:52:10,373 --> 01:52:12,443
You may kiss the bride.
You already did.

1601
01:52:12,733 --> 01:52:14,530
- Let's go.
- No, wait!

1602
01:52:14,813 --> 01:52:16,087
Hold it!

1603
01:52:16,453 --> 01:52:17,522
What is it?

1604
01:52:17,933 --> 01:52:20,083
Let me have this glass!

1605
01:52:20,413 --> 01:52:23,052
No, goddamn it!
What are you doing?!

1606
01:52:23,573 --> 01:52:26,406
Talk to the hand!
I'll be right back.

1607
01:52:26,693 --> 01:52:29,685
You know how long it took me
to fill that thing? All day!

1608
01:52:29,933 --> 01:52:32,686
This is unsanitary.
What is this?

1609
01:52:33,093 --> 01:52:34,731
- Break the glass.
- I'll get piss on my shoes!

1610
01:52:35,453 --> 01:52:36,727
You got to do this!

1611
01:52:37,493 --> 01:52:38,926
<i>Mazel tov</i>!

1612
01:52:41,133 --> 01:52:43,089
Come back here,
you little son of a bitch!

1613
01:52:43,413 --> 01:52:44,562
Pant, pant, blow.

1614
01:52:44,853 --> 01:52:46,127
Leo, please.

1615
01:52:47,733 --> 01:52:50,805
Your work is over here.
I think someone else needs you.

1616
01:52:55,933 --> 01:52:57,810
Good luck, Lorna, Riggs.

1617
01:53:01,373 --> 01:53:02,567
Thanks a lot.

1618
01:53:07,213 --> 01:53:08,771
Stick around.
Meet the kid.

1619
01:53:09,013 --> 01:53:11,083
Good luck, Lorna!

1620
01:53:16,773 --> 01:53:18,764
Here it comes.

1621
01:53:20,813 --> 01:53:22,007
Here he is.

1622
01:53:22,573 --> 01:53:25,610
He's looking right at you.
He knows it's you.

1623
01:53:30,253 --> 01:53:31,891
Rog, look what I found.

1624
01:53:32,493 --> 01:53:34,848
- Look at that.
- What a beauty!

1625
01:53:35,533 --> 01:53:37,251
Look at those eyes!

1626
01:53:37,853 --> 01:53:40,208
- He looks like his mother.
- Yes, he does.

1627
01:53:40,533 --> 01:53:41,488
Murtaugh!

1628
01:53:44,253 --> 01:53:45,572
No, Butters!

1629
01:53:46,013 --> 01:53:47,844
Butters' baby.
Better not be Murtaugh.

1630
01:53:48,173 --> 01:53:49,606
It's Butters.

1631
01:53:51,093 --> 01:53:52,606
Look at that baby.

1632
01:53:53,333 --> 01:53:54,812
Look at the hair.

1633
01:53:55,773 --> 01:53:57,411
That's my baby!

1634
01:53:58,013 --> 01:54:00,527
Look at her. You're so cute.
Look at you!

1635
01:54:00,773 --> 01:54:03,333
27 people, nobody thought
of bringing a camera?

1636
01:54:03,573 --> 01:54:05,086
Leo, your plastic's flaccid.

1637
01:54:05,453 --> 01:54:08,684
These machines wreck your plastic,
then give you the camera.

1638
01:54:09,053 --> 01:54:11,203
The camera doesn't work.
They're trying to...

1639
01:54:15,573 --> 01:54:16,926
What are you doing here?

1640
01:54:17,693 --> 01:54:19,126
Look at these two babies.

1641
01:54:19,373 --> 01:54:21,409
A little something from the squad.

1642
01:54:24,013 --> 01:54:26,322
- Give back the captain badges.
- Why?

1643
01:54:26,573 --> 01:54:29,724
Congratulations, you're sergeants again.
The city's self-insured.

1644
01:54:30,013 --> 01:54:31,924
I thought they'd make us president.

1645
01:54:33,053 --> 01:54:35,248
By the way, Grandpa,
you owe the chief one.

1646
01:54:35,573 --> 01:54:36,847
He went to the INS...

1647
01:54:37,053 --> 01:54:39,487
...and they're giving asylum
to the Hongs.

1648
01:54:39,933 --> 01:54:40,922
All right!

1649
01:54:42,653 --> 01:54:44,211
We're going to take a picture.

1650
01:54:48,373 --> 01:54:50,489
Squeeze together.
Candy stripers out.

1651
01:54:50,813 --> 01:54:52,087
Out! Okay. Out!

1652
01:54:52,813 --> 01:54:54,929
I can't.
There's not enough room.

1653
01:54:56,813 --> 01:54:58,485
You got to back up.

1654
01:54:59,253 --> 01:55:00,288
I'm taking big steps!

1655
01:55:00,613 --> 01:55:02,012
Get this guy to take it.

1656
01:55:02,293 --> 01:55:04,807
Doc, can you take a picture
of all of us?

1657
01:55:07,893 --> 01:55:10,009
It's my best man, after all.

1658
01:55:10,373 --> 01:55:11,852
Get my grandbaby in it too.

1659
01:55:12,133 --> 01:55:13,168
Are you all friends?

1660
01:55:13,493 --> 01:55:16,326
No. We're family!

1661
01:55:16,613 --> 01:55:17,409
Okay, on 3.

1662
01:55:17,693 --> 01:55:19,604
One, two, three!
